def: A person who is sixty years old.
Pertaining to, or obtained from, the horse-chestnut; as,esculic acid.
A European species of Saint John's-wort; the tutsan. SeeTutsan.
Slow; slowly, leisurely, and gracefully. When repeated, adagio,adagio, it directs the movement to be very slow.
The act of making noble. [Obs.] Dr. H. More.
The quality or state of being pert.
Not bent or arched; not bowed down. Byron.
A dread or intolerance of light. Sir T. Watson.
Dealing by enchantment; magical. Sir T. Browne.
